# Building on macOS

This page describes how to build the Live Background Removal Lite plugin on macOS.

## Prerequisites

- [Homebrew](https://brew.sh/)
- CMake (version 3.20 or later)
- Xcode (including Command Line Tools)
- Ninja (recommended)

## Installing Dependencies

Install required tools using Homebrew:

```sh
brew install cmake ninja
```

## Build Steps

1. Clone the repository.
2. Open a terminal and navigate to the project root directory.
3. Run the following commands:

### Standard Build

```sh
cmake --preset macos
cmake --build --preset macos
```

### Build for OBS (Homebrew version)

```sh
cmake --preset macos-homebrew
cmake --build --preset macos-homebrew
```

## Running Tests

```sh
cmake --preset macos-testing
cmake --build --preset macos-testing
ctest --preset macos-testing --rerun-failed --output-on-failure
```

## Testing the Plugin with OBS

After building, copy the plugin to the OBS plugins directory:

Standard version:
```sh
rm -rf ~/Library/Application\ Support/obs-studio/plugins/live-backgroundremoval-lite.plugin
cp -r ./build_macos/RelWithDebInfo/live-backgroundremoval-lite.plugin ~/Library/Application\ Support/obs-studio/plugins
```

Homebrew version:
```sh
rm -rf ~/Library/Application\ Support/obs-studio/plugins/live-backgroundremoval-lite.plugin
cp -r ./build_homebrew/RelWithDebInfo/live-backgroundremoval-lite.plugin ~/Library/Application\ Support/obs-studio/plugins
```

## Troubleshooting

- If the build fails due to outdated CMake or Xcode, please use the latest versions.
- If dependency installation fails, try updating Homebrew (`brew update`).
